Package assquad666.quoridor

Class Summary
AI AI is called to generate a move based on game state and a smartness of a move.
AIPlayer AIPlayer extends Player and represents an AI Player, which will generate moves.
Command Command is in charge of parsing a String of input and storing it into itself.
Game Game is in charge of storing Game states, asking for input to update them, playing, saving and displaying Games.
GameFactory Game factory is in charge of input, creating games, loading games.
Human Human extends Player and represents a Human Player, which will be prompted for input to move.
Move Move is in charge of storing moves informations(coordinates, if it's a wall, it's direction).
Player Player reprensents an abstract Player in the Game: it can be a human, or an AI.
Point Point is in charge of storing the coordinates of a square on the board.
Validator Validator is in charge of deciding if a move or a serie of moves is valid according to the games' rules.
Wall Wall represents a wall in the Game.
